https://sourceforge.net/apps/trac/sourceforge/wiki/Git

$ git clone ssh://USERNAME@fusion-linux.git.sourceforge.net/gitroot/fusion-linux/fusion-linux
$ cd fusion-linux
$ touch test
$ git add .
$ git push origin master

To access a Git repository, configure your Git client as follows (replace PROJECTNAME with the UNIX group name of the project, and REPONAME with the name of the git repository):

git://PROJECTNAME.git.sourceforge.net/gitroot/PROJECTNAME/REPONAME (read-only)
ssh://USERNAME@PROJECTNAME.git.sourceforge.net/gitroot/PROJECTNAME/REPONAME (read/write)



http://git-scm.com/

Creating and Commiting

$ cd (project-directory)
$ git init
$ (add some files)
$ git add .
$ git commit -m 'Initial commit'


# Remove the submodule
git rm --cached path/to/submodule

# add bunch of new files and folders
git add --all


# standard procedure when editing files
1. change some files
2. commit changes
 git commit -m 'comment'
3. upload changes
 git push origin master

# standard procedure when adding or deleting files
1. add or delete some file
2. scan all files to find new and deleted ones
 git add --all
3. commit changes
 git commit -m 'comment'
4. upload changes
 git push origin master
